{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-work-template-js","path":"/validating-knowledge-intersectoral-research-framework-city-science/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Problem</h2>\n<p>Intersectoral research combining <strong>Artificial Intelligence (AI)</strong>, <strong>social sciences</strong>, and <strong>urban planning</strong> is crucial for tackling complex urban challenges like climate change and public health. However, ensuring the <strong>validity</strong> of knowledge across these diverse fields is difficult due to different <strong>epistemic</strong> and <strong>ontological</strong> frameworks. Traditional metrics often fall short in capturing the interdisciplinary nature, leading to lower funding success and challenges in maintaining credibility and relevance.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.00000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/507e6/city_in_cs_sankey.webp 200w,\n/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/28a80/city_in_cs_sankey.webp 400w,\n/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/8d2ea/city_in_cs_sankey.webp 800w,\n/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/fb185/city_in_cs_sankey.webp 825w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/36ca5/city_in_cs_sankey.png 200w,\n/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/a3397/city_in_cs_sankey.png 400w,\n/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/a331c/city_in_cs_sankey.png 800w,\n/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/7f529/city_in_cs_sankey.png 825w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/f8fef0f372c2c2f674e4aa8c45523ac9/a331c/city_in_cs_sankey.png\"\n            alt=\"City and AI connecting social and computer sciences\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n<em>Figure 1. City and AI connecting social and computer sciences.</em></p>\n<h2>Method</h2>\n<p>We reviewed the most cited papers from <strong>2014 to 2024</strong> across AI, social sciences, and urban planning. The analysis focused on six dimensions:</p>\n<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Ontological</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Epistemological</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Methodological</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Teleological</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Axiological</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Valorization</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<p>Based on this, we developed a <strong>validation framework</strong> to guide researchers in selecting appropriate methodologies and epistemologies. The framework was tested through <strong>case studies</strong> and refined with input from experts in each field.</p>\n<h2>Findings</h2>\n<p>Our framework categorizes perspectives within the six dimensions, promoting a structured approach to validate intersectoral studies:</p>\n<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Ontological:</strong> Defining reality in city science and AI.</li>\n<li><strong>Epistemological:</strong> Understanding knowledge scope in interdisciplinary research.</li>\n<li><strong>Methodological:</strong> Choosing methods that integrate AI, social sciences, and urban planning.</li>\n<li><strong>Teleological:</strong> Aligning research with societal needs.</li>\n<li><strong>Axiological:</strong> Incorporating values and ethics.</li>\n<li><strong>Valorization:</strong> Ensuring practical impact.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<h2>Interactive Visualization</h2>\n<p><strong>Explore the detailed concepts <a href=\"https://mid-spaces.github.io/landing-page/network.html\">here</a>.</strong></p>\n<h2>Impact</h2>\n<p>This framework bridges disciplinary silos, enhancing the <strong>credibility</strong> and <strong>relevance</strong> of intersectoral research in city science. It provides a clear guide for researchers to adopt or avoid certain perspectives, ensuring <strong>socially accountable knowledge</strong>. Future steps include testing the framework in other domains, expanding stakeholder engagement, integrating with policy development, and developing educational programs.</p>\n<h2>Related Links</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.umontreal.ca/\">University of Montreal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://mila.quebec/en\">Mila - Quebec AI Institute</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://unesco-studio.umontreal.ca/\">UNESCO Chair in Urban Landscape</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Tags</h2>\n<div class=\"tags\">\n  <span class=\"tag\">Artificial Intelligence</span>\n  <span class=\"tag\">Urban Planning</span>\n  <span class=\"tag\">Intersectoral Reserach</span>\n  <span class=\"tag\">Knowledge Validation</span>\n  <span class=\"tag\">City Science</span>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Knowledge in Intersectoral Research","date":"2024-11-20","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/0a76a/network_analysis.png","srcSet":"/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/f52f1/network_analysis.png 350w,\n/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/577c5/network_analysis.png 700w,\n/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/0a76a/network_analysis.png 1400w","sizes":"(min-width: 1400px) 1400px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/7d945/network_analysis.avif 350w,\n/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/9c6c6/network_analysis.avif 700w,\n/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/c4579/network_analysis.avif 1400w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 1400px) 1400px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/c80d7/network_analysis.webp 350w,\n/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/54a9a/network_analysis.webp 700w,\n/static/d57d3fc7edd0808d6b8261252a2ac571/8b350/network_analysis.webp 1400w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1400px) 1400px, 100vw"}]},"width":1400,"height":1242}}},"description":"A framework to validate knowledge in AI, social sciences, and urban planning for credible city science.","author":"Rashid Mushkani, University of Montreal, Mila - Quebec AI Institute","path":"validating-knowledge-intersectoral-research-framework-city-science"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"validating-knowledge-intersectoral-research-framework-city-science"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}